{
  "stem": "942.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And I can't say that I was too sad about that, because there was no Hebrew school.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I was kind of happy about that, you know?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "So life went on.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And here comes 1943.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "My father and uncle came back from the forced labor camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And I think they found a way of handling things, that they found a job in a lumber mill about 30, 40 kilometers from my town.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And both of them were working there as essential labor, so they will not be taken away to forced labor camp.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And I know that they came home-- this was all of 1943, approximately-- they came home every Friday afternoon for the Sabbath.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And my mother had breads baked for them and some other stuff, you know?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And after the Sabbath, Sunday morning, early morning, they packed their backpacks and they went to the train station.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And they were off for a whole week again to do this labor.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And this is the way they kept themselves out of the labor camps.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And in 1943, as well, I left home.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I went to this town of Kasha.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I became an apprentice at a furrier place.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I lived with some relatives.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I lived there and I ate with them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I had to get up every morning, about 5:30 in the morning, to get down to this place of business where the furrier was.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, you know, as an apprentice, I had to clean the stove, take the clinkers and the ashes out every morning, and sweep the floors, and put everything in order, and start the fire.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I was given the so-called dirty jobs.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The furs, after they are repaired-- or before-- they have to be cleaned.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
